x4freetext: By compiler. Lederer,et al.,Table of isotopes,6th ed.,
show a metastable state (H-life = 43 day) in Cd-115
which decays nearly 100% by beta-. Authors do not
mention possible effects of this state. Tabulated
data have been assumed to represent the partial capture
cross section for population of the ground state.
Half-life values assumed by the authors may be
superseded.

VOF.- Half-life added.-
By compiler. Lederer,et al.,Table of isotopes,6th ed.,
indicate about 2.5% decay of the 1.3-min metastable
state in Dy-165 by beta-. The authors apparently
have assumed that the metastable state decays entirely
by isomeric transition to the ground state (H-life =
139 min) of Dy-165.
The partial cross sections for production of the ground
and metastable states of Dy-165 were determined
individually later by the same authors, see Nucl.Phys.
A117,545(1968) and entries 30086.009 and .008 respect.
